                    "attribs": {
                        "\"length\"": "\"12\"",
                        "\"nightride\"": "1"
                    },
                    "description": "This section of the CDT is all singletrack, some buff and sweet, some rocky but &lt;br /&gt;<br />&lt;br /&gt;<br />no too much so.  Check &quot;CDT Goldstone South&quot; for the CDT section heading &lt;br /&gt;<br />&lt;br /&gt;<br />north from this same spot.&lt;br /&gt;<br />&lt;br /&gt;<br />&lt;br /&gt;<br />&lt;br /&gt;<br />From the parking spot, follow the 2-track through an old hunting camp looking &lt;br /&gt;<br />&lt;br /&gt;<br />for the classic USFS tree blazes (upside down exclamation point scraped into the &lt;br /&gt;<br />&lt;br /&gt;<br />bark) marking the CDT soon after.  These blazes will mark the trail from here on &lt;br /&gt;<br />&lt;br /&gt;<br />until you reach the high meadows and some cairns at the turnaround point 6 &lt;br /&gt;<br />&lt;br /&gt;<br />miles later.  The trail is wooded but if you are patient you will be rewarded with &lt;br /&gt;<br />&lt;br /&gt;<br />some huge views into Montana and of Idaho's southern Lemhi Mountains.",
